Subject: [PATCH 15/46] fix(priorities): allow unranked sources to update their
 own values
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

When sourceRanking is configured, an unranked source competing against
itself was treated as HIGHEST precedence (as latest) but LOWEST (as
incoming), effectively throttling it to one update per
unknownSourceTimeout. This caused N2K switch state confirmations to
fail because the device response delta was filtered out.

Add early return in isPreferredValue when incoming source matches the
latest source — a source refreshing its own value is never a priority
conflict.
