From c0403f1860145ac3e30b9b484da27e41c7c1e41a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 09:27:15 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 21/46] fix(priorities): narrow hold-timeout override to
 known-vs-unknown

The previous commit changed holdTimeout to always use the winner's
timeout, which broke existing tests that rely on the incoming
(lower-ranked) source's timeout governing switchover in known-vs-
known scenarios (e.g. path-level priority lists).

Restrict the override to the case Scott actually hit: a known source
is winning and an unknown source tries to take over. In that case
the unknown source must outwait both unknownSourceTimeout AND the
winner's configured timeout. For known-vs-known competition the
original semantic (incoming's timeout governs) is preserved.

Add tests covering the known-holds-off-unknown case and the
unknown-does-not-self-renew case.
---
