Remove the Source Ranking concept that users reported as confusing:

- Delete the Source Ranking card, store slice, ws event, REST
  endpoints, engine parameter, and docs. Any pre-existing
  `settings.sourceRanking` in settings.json is silently ignored.
- Simplify deltaPriority: the "known source" test is now purely
  path-level. Path-level semantics are unchanged; all path-level
  unit tests pass.

Make per-path priorities easier to understand:

- Rename the column "Timeout (ms)" -> "Fallback after (ms)" so the
  semantics (silence threshold on higher-priority sources before
  THIS row wins) are explicit.
- Rewrite the inline help to introduce the mental model: top row
  = preferred, other rows list how long the preferred source must
  be silent before they are allowed to take over.
- Add an inline SVG timeline and a committed docs/img version
  showing preferred-active -> silence -> backup-takes-over, with
  the "Fallback after" arrow annotation.
- Add a worked example with two GPS receivers.
- Reduce the default fallback for new rows from 60000 ms to
  5000 ms so first-time users get usable behaviour out of the box.
- Correct the stale "120 seconds" reference (actual default for
