From a172371b541070aa3a410caac9a1c32c8f6e9403 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 14:05:21 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 30/46] fix(ui): resume Data Browser updates after server
 restart
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

After WebSocket reconnect, startDiscovery() ran on the new connection
but currentPaths still held the path set from the old connection.
The next requestPaths() saw the same paths, the similarity check
passed, and the subscription was skipped — so the server never sent
updates on the new connection.

Reset currentPaths in startDiscovery() so requestPaths() always
re-sends subscriptions on a fresh connection.
---
 .../src/views/DataBrowser/GranularSubscriptionManager.ts      | 4 ++++
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+)

diff --git a/packages/server-admin-ui/src/views/DataBrowser/GranularSubscriptionManager.ts b/packages/server-admin-ui/src/views/DataBrowser/GranularSubscriptionManager.ts
index 0e076046a..bf717cb45 100644
--- a/packages/server-admin-ui/src/views/DataBrowser/GranularSubscriptionManager.ts
+++ b/packages/server-admin-ui/src/views/DataBrowser/GranularSubscriptionManager.ts
@@ -79,6 +79,10 @@ class GranularSubscriptionManager {
       subscribe: [] // Empty initially, will be populated by requestPaths
     })
 
+    // Reset currentPaths so the next requestPaths() re-sends subscriptions
+    // on this (possibly new) WebSocket connection, even if the path set
+    // hasn't changed.
+    this.currentPaths = new Set()
     this.state = STATE.SUBSCRIBED
 
     // If there are pending paths from before WebSocket was ready, apply them now

From c0d41b241e6ef5d2884bbf89733712918634c752 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 15:10:01 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 31/46] feat(ui): redesign Data Browser controls and
 group-by-source view

Replace three toggle switches with two dropdowns + sliding Pause:

  Context | View [By Path / By Source] | Sources [Priority filtered /
  All sources] | Raw [As Value / As Raw] | Pause

By Source now keeps the full table (path, value, timestamp, source)
with source-group section headers injected at each source boundary,
instead of the old SourceView that dropped values and timestamps.

In All Sources mode, a green checkmark marks the preferred source
for each path so users can see which source would win under
filtering.

In Priority Filtered mode, client-side deduplication ensures only
the preferred source's entry is shown per path, even when the
server's initial cache dump contains multiple sources.

Simplify GranularSubscriptionManager: remove the two-step
unsubscribe-all/resubscribe pattern that killed announceNewPaths
during initial discovery and caused paths to stop appearing. New
subscribe messages now always include announceNewPaths and replace
the existing subscription directly. New paths that aren't yet
subscribed always trigger resubscription regardless of the
similarity threshold.

Delete SourceView.tsx (replaced by grouped VirtualizedDataTable).
Add SourceGroupHeader.tsx for source section headers.
Add usePreferredSourceByPath store hook.
