From 2fb1539bcab512a3b321b790e96e8cbafb4941fd Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Apr 2026 14:25:27 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 42/46] docs+code: align with maintainer guidance on docs and
 comments
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Docs:
- Remove the 'Source Priority: Global Source Ranking Removed' entry
  from breaking_changes.md. Source Ranking was added and removed
  within this branch and never shipped, so there is no breaking
  change for users to be aware of.
- Trim the detailed REST API sections in source-priority.md and
  n2k-device-management.md (JSON request/response schemas, parameter
  tables, value ranges, status codes). Replace with short conceptual
  descriptions and pointers to the route handlers as the
  authoritative source. Implementation-level details belong in code,
  not docs that drift.

Code:
- Remove echo comments that simply restated what the next line of
  code already said (DataBrowser path/source grouping, n2k-discovery
  sort and label-attach loops).
- Remove implementation-history note from sourceref-migration that
  explained why deltaCache cleanup is no longer counted in migrated
  — that belongs in commit messages, not in the source.
---
