From 43b1ee8d0318a3677f3a53ea0fa83b019886ffb5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 03:54:02 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 43/46] fix(n2k): default useCamelCompat to off to match master
 behaviour

The CamelCase Compat toggle for N2K providers was defaulting to on
in this branch, silently opting users into legacy field-name output.
Master ships without this defaulting on, so keep parity: both the
canboatjs stream default and the UI checkbox default are now off.
Users who need legacy-compat field names for older plugins can
enable the toggle explicitly per connection.
