From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 06:15:08 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 44/46] fix(n2k): restore useCanName toggle to match master
 behaviour

The 'Use Can NAME in source data' toggle exists on master in
BasicProvider.tsx and is wired through n2k-signalk.ts. This branch
had accidentally removed the gating logic, forcing canName-based
$source on everyone and breaking Node-RED flows / ACLs / plugins
that were written against address-based refs.

Restored: the useCanName gate in isFiltered and _transform, the
UseCanNameInput component, and the Can NAME vs Address column label
switch in N2KFilters. Default stays off (matches master); users who
want stable source refs across bus reshuffles opt in per connection.
