From d86d7851426d2b3fd726dbaef41eac344b895288 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dirkwa <dirkwahrtheit@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 07:07:19 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 46/46] feat(priorities): introduce Priority Groups UI

Sources that share paths are auto-grouped via connected-components
on multiSourcePaths. Each group card supports drag-and-drop ranking
(dnd-kit with keyboard support), an inline collapsible list of
path-level overrides, and a path-chip overview. Saving a ranking
fans out to sourcePriorities for every shared path that has no
explicit override; override detection compares current entries
against the saved (baseline) group order so reordering a group
does not mass-create overrides.

priorityGroups is a new UI-layer setting persisted in settings.json;
the delta engine remains untouched. A new WS event PRIORITYGROUPS
and REST GET/PUT /skServer/priorityGroups keep clients in sync, and
sourceref-migration rewrites sourceRefs inside priorityGroups[].sources.
